<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued March 27 at 11:24PM CDT until March 28 at 12:00AM CDT by NWS Austin-San Antonio</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL MIDNIGHT CDT
FOR SOUTHWESTERN EDWARDS AND EAST CENTRAL VAL VERDE COUNTIES...
At 1124 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 8 miles southwest
of Carta Valley, or 15 miles south of Loma Alta, moving northeast at
20 mph.
HAZARD...Quarter size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Damage to vehicles is expected.
This severe storm will be near...
Carta Valley around 1145 PM CDT.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;50 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
